    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "4) Componente com callback (entrada + saída)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Componentes úteis recebem dados e expõem callbacks. Isso mantém o fluxo claro: o componente não decide o que o app faz; ele apenas informa que algo aconteceu."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "lang": "javascript",
      "content": "function createCounter({ initial = 0, onChange }) {\n  let value = initial;\n\n  const root = document.createElement('div');\n  const btnMinus = document.createElement('button');\n  const btnPlus = document.createElement('button');\n  const out = document.createElement('span');\n\n  btnMinus.textContent = '-';\n  btnPlus.textContent = '+';\n\n  function render() {\n    out.textContent = String(value);\n  }\n\n  btnMinus.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    value -= 1;\n    render();\n    onChange?.(value);\n  });\n\n  btnPlus.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    value += 1;\n    render();\n    onChange?.(value);\n  });\n\n  root.append(btnMinus, out, btnPlus);\n  render();\n  return root;\n}\n\nconst counter = createCounter({ initial: 10, onChange: (v) => console.log('valor=', v) });\ndocument.body.appendChild(counter);",
